 -total\n 30.85%   79.445      1 Template:Store_locations_list\n 26.25%   67.593      1 Template:Infobox_Bonuses\n 18.99%   48.894      1 Template:Infobox_Item\n 15.06%   38.790      4 Template:Navbox\n 12.78%   32.910      1 Template:Hallowed_Sepulchre\n  3.62%    9.332      1 Template:CiteTwitter\n  2.42%    6.229      1 Template:CombatStyles\n  1.92%    4.953      4 Template:Subject_changes\n  1.80%    4.648      1 Template:Ctg\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key en_osrswiki:pcache:idhash:266001-0!canonical and timestamp 20220421113820 and revision id 14254835. Serialized with PHP.\n -->\n</div>","rawContent":"{{Infobox Item\n|name = Hallowed hammer\n|image = [[File:Hallowed hammer.png]]\n|release = [[4 June]] [[2020]]\n|update = Darkmeyer\n|members = Yes\n|quest = No\n|tradeable = No\n|placeholder = Yes\n|equipable = Yes\n|stackable = No\n|noteable = No\n|options = Wield\n|destroy = Drop\n|examine = Removes the chance of bending nails within the Hallowed Sepulchre.\n|value = 10000\n|alchable = No\n|weight = 0.020\n|id = 24727\n}}\n[[File:Hallowed hammer detail.png|left|120px]]\nThe '''hallowed hammer''' is an item that will never break nails inside the [[Hallowed Sepulchre]] (regardless of the plank and nail combination used). It can be purchased from the [[Mysterious Hallowed Goods]] shop for 100 [[hallowed mark]]s. Unlike the other hallowed equipment, the hammer does not need to be equipped in order for its effect to work.\n\nThe hallowed hammer '''cannot''' be used in place of a normal [[hammer]] outside the Hallowed Sepulchre.\n\nThe hammer also counts as a Saradomin item for the purposes of recharging your run [[energy]] at the Magical Obelisks at the end of each floor, as well as in [[God Wars Dungeon]].\n\n{{Infobox Bonuses\n|astab = 0\n|aslash = 0\n|acrush = 0\n|amagic = 0\n|arange = 0\n|dstab = 0\n|dslash = 0\n|dcrush = 0\n|dmagic = 0\n|drange = 0\n|str = 0\n|rstr = 0\n|mdmg = 0\n|prayer = 0\n|slot = weapon\n|speed = 4\n|attackrange = 1\n|combatstyle = Blunt\n|image = [[File:Hallowed hammer equipped.png|160px]]\n|altimage = [[File:Hallowed hammer equipped female.png|160px]]\n}}\n\n==Combat styles==\n{{CombatStyles|Blunt}}\n\n==Shop locations==\n{{Store locations list|Hallowed hammer}}\n\n==Changes==\n{{Subject changes header}}\n{{Subject changes\n|date = 2 July 2020\n|update = Poll 71 and Death Feedback Changes\n|change = \n*The hallowed hammer is now labeled as a member's item.\n*The examine text on the hallowed hammer has been slightly changed; previously, the examine text was \"Removes the chance of bending nails in the Hallowed Sepulchre.\"\n}}\n{{Subject changes\n|date = 25 June 2020\n|update = Death Changes\n|change = The examine text on the hallowed hammer has been changed to reflect its buff from the previous week's update. Previously, the examine text was \"Reduces the chance of bending nails in the Hallowed Sepulchre.\"\n}}\n{{Subject changes\n|date = 18 June 2020\n|update = Poll 71 and Darkmeyer Updates\n|change = The Hallowed hammer now has a 100% chance to not bend nails regardless of the plank and nail combination used.\n}}\n{{Subject changes\n|date = 12 June 2020\n|update = Darkmeyer Improvements\n|poll =\n|change = All Hallowed items can no longer be alchemised.\n}}\n{{Subject changes footer}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* The Hallowed Hammer does not work outside the Sepulchre because making it usable in other areas of RuneScape would require rewriting all hammer-related code across the entire game, a very large and time-consuming endeavour.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://mobile.twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1300821691040497665|date=1 September 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.vn/F3sB3|archivedate=7 March 2021|quote=[Would it be possible for the Hallowed Hammer to act like a normal hammer while un-equipped?] It would - but it would require all hammer-related code across the game to be rewritten.|notes=|name=|group=}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Hallowed Sepulchre}}"}